CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 4, 1946, pg. 15 reads: "Impressive Nuptials - The marriage of Miss Myrtle Ayers, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. John Ayers of 110 Fullerton Street, and Samuel Johnson Jr. of 1419 Hazel Street, was solemnized recently in parsonage of Bethel AME Church by the Rev. Mr. Robinson. Miss Edna Cleveland was matron of honor.  Edward Alexander was best man.  The nuptials were followed by a reception. - Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Group portrait five men, four women, boy, and girl, including groom Samuel Johnson Jr. and bride Myrtle Ayers Johnson, cutting two tiered cake, posed in parsonage of Bethel AME Church
